<item>
            <title>[WICKET-5398] XmlPullParser fails to properly parse from String with encoding declaration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5398</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When parsing from a string, XmlPullParser fails if the encoding from the XML declaration is different than the system&apos;s file encoding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples:&lt;br/&gt;
   -Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1&lt;br/&gt;
   parser.parse(&quot;&amp;lt;?xml encoding=&apos;UTF-8&apos; ?&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span id=&apos;umlaut-&#228;&#246;&#252;&apos;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8&lt;br/&gt;
   parser.parse(&quot;&amp;lt;?xml encoding=&apos;ISO-8859-1&apos; ?&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span id=&apos;umlaut-&#228;&#246;&#252;&apos;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both fail because the string is read with the system&apos;s file encoding while the parser expects the stream to be encoded in the declarated encoding.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
